/// @author Tyler Benton
/// @page helpers/mixins
/// @description
/// Used as a helper to add svgs as background images.
/// ##### Things to you need to know.
///  - You don't need a `doctype` for your svg.
///  - Start your svg with the `<svg {get($svg, base-attributes)}>`. This will add the necessary attributes to make sure the svg will scale properly.
///  - Declair viewbox in the `svg` tag. If you don't know what that is then just add `<svg {get($svg, base-attributes)} viewBox="0 0 100 100">` instead of the line above.
///  - Wether you're writing the svg as a single line or multi line, you must wrap each line in single quote marks(`'`).
///  - If you're writing a multi line svg then you must and add a comma(`,`) at the end of each line(except the last line).
///  - Use only double quotes(`"`) inside of your svg code.
///  - Wrap your svg with single quotes like this `'<svg>...</svg>'`
///  - If the svg isn't displaying as expected try the following
///   - Replace `#` with `{get($svg, "#")}`
///   - Replace `%` with `{get($svg, "%")}`
///   - Replace `/` with `{get($svg, "/")}`. Try replacing `</style>` with `<{get($svg, "/")}style> first) before you replace all of them
///
/// @arg {string} - The svg code you want to add wrapped in a string
///
/// @markup {styl} (example="fasle") - **Example: basic**
/// .foo {
///   background: url(svg('someurl.svg')) 0 0/contain no-repeat;
/// }
///
/// @markup {css} (example="false") - **Output: basic**
/// .foo {
///   background: url('data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,<svg xmlns="http:///www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="100%" height="100%" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" viewBox="0 0 50 50"><circle class="path" cx="50%" cy="50%" r="20" fill="black" stroke-width="6" stroke-miterlimit="10" /></svg>') 0 0/contain no-repeat;
/// }
use('svg-import.js')
svg($url)
  'data:image/svg+xml;charset=UTF-8,' + svg-import($url)